Get busy livin’ or get busy dyin’

I’ve always had one main focus and that’s to produce the best quality image I can whether it’s how I shoot, color grade, or edit. I think I don’t give myself enough credit for my progression so this post fixes that. My drive to take risks and chase locations has never been higher and I’m on a roll to be the best videographer I can be. 21 year-old Heber got back in the game. 22 year-old Heber will be the game😤

2 DAYS IN PATAGONIA🦙

I’m a man of last-minute trips. Never did I ever think a trip down to the southernmost part of South America would be that, but it was. Patagonia has been high on the bucket list for years and the opportunity presented itself right when I felt ready to capture it in its awesomeness.

You don’t need to travel far to experience what traveling is like. Over the last few years, I’ve discovered that even my home can be considered a destination. Yes, I’m fortunate to live in a place that has mountains, but I used to live on the east coast, where all there is for hundreds of miles is forest and farmland. That’s where I began to get into videography! There were definitely spots and angles I thought looked amazing, and it proved to me that the east coast had a unique vibe that other places didn’t👌

The best way I can really comprehend all of this obvious creation is if I create myself and capture it all through Timelapse photography. I don’t know why I’m so obsessed with this art form now but I’m sure it means something greater somewhere else🔭

The best part is… I’m only 22.

I owe it to myself for beginning that rollercoaster of a learning experience 6 years ago. Filmmaking isn’t easy to figure out and understand. It’s a matter of training your eyes, solving problems, and evoking feelings through a lens. I’ll never stop learning and I’ll never stop reaping the rewards from my experience.

Work hard. It really does pay off.

I wanna give credit to those who inspired me through the years to deliver the best feelings and images possible. Thank you for giving your best effort @justkay @robstrok @samkolder @andrewjmes @jacques_crafford @theqazman

This is FAROE🇫🇴

This place has been #1 on my bucket list ever since I was 15 years old. Nowhere else can you find steep cliffs, shaggy livestock, and crazy island views all in one. I’m super blessed I was able to see this place in all it had to offer.

When visiting the Faroe Islands, please be considerate of your actions and show respect to the local community. With a recent surge in tourism, it’s super important to maintain a positive relationship between visitors and the locals who call Faroe home.
